What is APR?APR stands for Annual Percentage Rate. It's a measure used to compare the yearly cost of borrowing money or earning interest on an investment. The APR includes not only the interest rate but also any additional fees or costs associated with the loan, such as origination fees or other charges.

In essence, it provides a more comprehensive picture of what you'll actually pay for a loan each year. It's important to understand that while a lower APR can mean less cost over the life of the loan, a higher APR means more cost. Therefore, when comparing loans or credit products, it's crucial to look at the APR rather than just the interest rate.yes
